HEADWORD: Handiwork
<hw>Hand"i*work`</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧*w⟦ucir⟧rk`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OE. <ets>handiwerc</ets>, AS. <ets>handgeweorc</ets>;
<ets>hand</ets> hand + <ets>geweorc</ets> work; prefix <ets>ge-</ets> +
<ets>weorc</ets>. See <er>Work</er>.]</ety> <def>Work done by the hands;
hence, any work done personally.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The firmament showeth his <qex>handiwork</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ps.
xix. 1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Handkercher</ent>⟦br⟧
